# SMS Spam Classifier 

A Machine Learning project that classifies SMS messages as **Ham** (legitimate) or **Spam** using Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Naive Bayes algorithms.

##  Overview
This project involves building an end-to-end machine learning pipeline to detect spam messages. It includes data cleaning, exploratory data analysis (EDA), text preprocessing (stemming, stopword removal), and model building.

##  Tech Stack
- **Language:** Python
- **Libraries:** Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, NLTK, Matplotlib, Seaborn, WordCloud
- **Algorithms:** Multinomial Naive Bayes (Best performing), Gaussian NB, Bernoulli NB
- **Vectorization:** TF-IDF Vectorizer

##  Features
- **Data Cleaning:** Handles missing values and removes duplicates.
- **EDA:** Visualizes the distribution of spam vs. ham using pie charts and histograms.
- **Text Preprocessing:** 
    - Lowercase conversion
    - Tokenization
    - Removal of special characters, stopwords, and punctuation
    - Stemming (using PorterStemmer)
- **Modeling:** Compares multiple Naive Bayes classifiers to find the highest precision model.
- **Persistence:** Saves the trained model and vectorizer using \`pickle\` for deployment.

## 📊 Performance
The **Multinomial Naive Bayes** with **TF-IDF Vectorization** (max_features=3000) was chosen as the final model due to its high precision score.

## 📂 Project Structure
